1
00:00:00,480 --> 00:00:04,840
One, two, three, four, five,
six, seven, eight, nine, ten.

2
00:00:04,880 --> 00:00:06,053
One, two, three...

3
00:00:06,093 --> 00:00:09,417
An 11-year-old boy. He fell into a river
and drowned. Currently in cardiac arrest.

4
00:00:09,457 --> 00:00:11,852
Hayato! Hayato!

5
00:00:12,120 --> 00:00:13,473
One, two, three.

6
00:00:15,603 --> 00:00:17,580
Doctor, please!

7
00:00:17,620 --> 00:00:18,620
Please, save Hayato!

8
00:00:18,648 --> 00:00:20,827
Sir, we're going to treat him now!

9
00:00:20,867 --> 00:00:22,173
- Get the Ambu bag.
- Okay!

10
00:00:22,353 --> 00:00:23,560
He's in your hands.

11
00:00:28,763 --> 00:00:30,010
He's cold.

12
00:00:30,703 --> 00:00:31,896
It's hypothermia.

13
00:00:31,936 --> 00:00:33,210
How long was he underwater?

14
00:00:33,250 --> 00:00:34,941
We believe it was close to an hour.

15
00:00:34,981 --> 00:00:35,983
An hour?!

16
00:00:36,023 --> 00:00:37,795
- Core temp?
- It's 17.4 degrees.

17
00:00:37,835 --> 00:00:39,863
- Warm him. Get an electric blanket.
- Understood.

18
00:00:39,903 --> 00:00:40,915
Ventilate.

19
00:00:40,955 --> 00:00:42,163
Yes!

20
00:00:46,316 --> 00:00:48,320
No good! Asystole!

21
00:00:48,360 --> 00:00:51,159
Doctor! PCPS isn't available!

22
00:00:51,306 --> 00:00:53,206
We warm him from inside.

23
00:00:53,253 --> 00:00:55,020
Insert chest tubes bilaterally.

24
00:00:55,060 --> 00:00:58,813
Infuse 40°C saline
into the chest cavity for lavage.

25
00:00:58,960 --> 00:01:00,000
Prep for drainage!

26
00:01:00,040 --> 00:01:01,240
Right away!

27
00:01:17,790 --> 00:01:20,288
Doctor! It's been 60 minutes
since the lavage started.

28
00:01:20,328 --> 00:01:21,390
Core temp?

29
00:01:21,430 --> 00:01:22,976
It's 30.4 degrees.

30
00:01:24,870 --> 00:01:26,170
Continue saline infusion.

31
00:01:26,210 --> 00:01:27,343
Warm up more as well.

32
00:01:27,383 --> 00:01:28,590
Yes.

33
00:01:51,063 --> 00:01:52,270
Resume.

34
00:01:56,276 --> 00:01:57,596
Dr. Yakushiji?

35
00:01:58,616 --> 00:02:00,276
What are you doing? Resume now.

36
00:02:03,820 --> 00:02:05,030
Move!

37
00:02:10,110 --> 00:02:11,316
But...

38
00:02:12,790 --> 00:02:16,976
We've been at this for over an hour,
and there's still no heartbeat.

39
00:02:19,223 --> 00:02:20,725
Doctor!

40
00:02:21,050 --> 00:02:24,176
It's no use! We have to stop!

41
00:02:25,150 --> 00:02:26,443
You have to live.

42
00:02:28,310 --> 00:02:29,523
Come on!

43
00:02:35,290 --> 00:02:36,523
Come on!

44
00:02:37,970 --> 00:02:39,356
Two minutes have passed.

45
00:02:51,170 --> 00:02:53,841
Good, there's still a chance.
Get the DC ready!

46
00:02:53,881 --> 00:02:55,129
Yes!

47
00:03:03,250 --> 00:03:06,910
Chairwoman, what is the meaning
of assigning Dr. Anno to Surgery?

48
00:03:06,950 --> 00:03:10,622
Putting that troublemaker
on our surgical team!

49
00:03:10,662 --> 00:03:11,662
It's outrageous!

50
00:03:11,690 --> 00:03:14,230
- Calm down, please.
- My apologies.

51
00:03:14,270 --> 00:03:16,550
Nothing's been decided yet.

52
00:03:16,550 --> 00:03:17,690
What do you mean?

53
00:03:17,730 --> 00:03:19,702
If we shut down the ER,

54
00:03:19,742 --> 00:03:23,523
it'd be a waste to let a surgeon
as skilled as Anno go to another hospital.

55
00:03:23,563 --> 00:03:24,763
True.

56
00:03:25,230 --> 00:03:30,670
Transfer her to Surgery,
and she becomes a valuable asset.

57
00:03:31,250 --> 00:03:33,736
It was Dr. Tamon's brilliant idea.

58
00:03:35,230 --> 00:03:39,635
You just said "if" the ER were
to be shut down.

59
00:03:39,675 --> 00:03:41,563
So the closure isn't decided yet?

60
00:03:41,570 --> 00:03:46,230
To make the new hospital a reality,
I believe shutting it down is inevitable.

61
00:03:46,876 --> 00:03:52,590
Well, the ER is nothing
but a burden to us anyway.

62
00:03:52,690 --> 00:03:57,990
But who'd have thought Dr. Tamoo...
I mean, Dr. Tamon would axe the ER!

63
00:03:58,203 --> 00:04:00,670
Quite a surprise.

64
00:04:00,976 --> 00:04:05,150
Your time abroad gave you quite
the change of brain... I mean, heart.

65
00:04:06,896 --> 00:04:11,063
There are other hospitals in this area
that can take emergency patients.

66
00:04:11,550 --> 00:04:16,363
As long as hospitals coordinate,
patients' lives will be saved as before.

67
00:04:19,250 --> 00:04:21,980
Was Hayato's father okay?

68
00:04:22,090 --> 00:04:23,350
He seems calmer now.

69
00:04:23,846 --> 00:04:27,973
Good. He was so shaken up,
I was really worried.

70
00:04:28,700 --> 00:04:34,958
Actually, my own son was once brought here
by ambulance after a car accident.

71
00:04:35,816 --> 00:04:37,900
My legs froze, and I couldn't move.

72
00:04:39,602 --> 00:04:41,029
Even though I'm a nurse.

73
00:04:41,109 --> 00:04:44,756
Anyone would react that way seeing
their own child hurt right in front of them.

74
00:04:44,870 --> 00:04:48,100
No matter how trained you are,
you're still a parent.

75
00:04:48,140 --> 00:04:52,356
Still, I never expected
Hayato's heartbeat to come back.

76
00:04:52,536 --> 00:04:54,800
Dr. Ashura really is amazing.

77
00:05:09,170 --> 00:05:10,396
Dr. Anno.

78
00:05:11,116 --> 00:05:12,323
What?

79
00:05:15,410 --> 00:05:17,010
I'm sorry!

80
00:05:20,696 --> 00:05:22,098
I gave up...

81
00:05:23,530 --> 00:05:25,603
on doing the chest compressions.

82
00:05:28,820 --> 00:05:31,423
River water's still cold this time of year.

83
00:05:33,880 --> 00:05:39,140
In cold water, survival is possible
even after being submerged for over an hour.

84
00:05:41,040 --> 00:05:43,156
That's why I kept performing resuscitation.

85
00:05:46,230 --> 00:05:47,823
I didn't know that.

86
00:05:53,880 --> 00:05:59,306
If you'd been the only one there,
that child would be dead by now.

87
00:06:04,003 --> 00:06:06,600
Hesitation on the battlefield is fatal.

88
00:06:08,520 --> 00:06:13,820
Resident or not, take responsibility
for the patient in front of you.

89
00:06:18,183 --> 00:06:19,383
Understood!

90
00:06:29,412 --> 00:06:33,296
Dr. Ashura

91
00:06:33,380 --> 00:06:35,340
Please, I'm begging you!

92
00:06:35,380 --> 00:06:38,293
I told you that if Dr. Anno breaks
the rules again,

93
00:06:38,466 --> 00:06:43,240
you'd be demoted for failing
to manage her, didn't I?

94
00:06:43,840 --> 00:06:44,873
No...

95
00:06:44,913 --> 00:06:50,180
Effective today, you are relieved
of your position as Head of the ER.

96
00:06:50,810 --> 00:06:52,043
Please!

97
00:06:52,840 --> 00:06:56,596
One more chance!
Just give me one more chance!

98
00:06:57,080 --> 00:06:58,419
Please!

99
00:07:00,893 --> 00:07:02,993
If you insist that much...

100
00:07:03,686 --> 00:07:04,886
Very well.

101
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:07,080
Thank you!

102
00:07:07,120 --> 00:07:10,756
But there will be no more second chances.

103
00:07:12,520 --> 00:07:17,000
This is your very last chance.

104
00:07:21,313 --> 00:07:22,640
What's wrong?

105
00:07:22,800 --> 00:07:26,676
The director chewed me out
for our overtime costs being too high.

106
00:07:26,960 --> 00:07:29,963
If he's complaining,
tell him to hire more staff.

107
00:07:30,366 --> 00:07:34,500
We're in the red year-round,
so it won't happen.

108
00:07:34,540 --> 00:07:38,020
But we get tons of patients
every day. We're swamped.

109
00:07:38,440 --> 00:07:40,220
So why are we in the red?

110
00:07:40,230 --> 00:07:42,720
- Intubation, 5,000 yen.
- Huh?

111
00:07:42,760 --> 00:07:45,000
CPR for 30 minutes, 2,500 yen.

112
00:07:45,040 --> 00:07:47,060
Chest tube drainage, 2,750 yen.

113
00:07:47,100 --> 00:07:49,283
Defibrillation, 35,000 yen.

114
00:07:49,996 --> 00:07:51,273
Think that's expensive?

115
00:07:51,280 --> 00:07:53,100
Uh... is it?

116
00:07:53,140 --> 00:07:56,300
- A heart valve replacement costs a million.
- That's insane!

117
00:07:56,340 --> 00:08:00,123
Yet the revenue hospitals get is
absurdly low.

118
00:08:00,163 --> 00:08:03,562
They need extra staff
for nights and holidays,

119
00:08:03,602 --> 00:08:04,956
so labor costs pile up.

120
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:06,156
No wonder it's a deficit.

121
00:08:06,196 --> 00:08:09,563
ER patients can come at any time,
regardless of the hour.

122
00:08:09,603 --> 00:08:13,780
The Surgery Department brings in
far more money than the ER.

123
00:08:14,783 --> 00:08:17,920
The unprofitable ER will be shut down soon.

124
00:08:19,420 --> 00:08:23,110
Dr. Yakushiji, do you plan
to become an emergency physician?

125
00:08:23,236 --> 00:08:29,306
No, no way! Once my residency is
over, I'm taking over my family's clinic.

126
00:08:30,180 --> 00:08:33,643
The pneumonia patient is in the ICU.
Call me if BP drops below 90.

127
00:08:33,783 --> 00:08:34,989
Understood.

128
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:40,300
I intend to shut down
the emergency department.

129
00:08:41,700 --> 00:08:44,109
Maybe Dr. Ashura's relieved, too.

130
00:08:44,260 --> 00:08:48,320
She's been fighting all alone
the entire time Dr. Tamon was away.

131
00:09:10,203 --> 00:09:12,203
Have you thought about the divorce?

132
00:09:22,143 --> 00:09:23,343
Yes.

133
00:09:23,840 --> 00:09:27,040
I want you to reconsider the divorce.

134
00:09:27,220 --> 00:09:28,375
I already told you.

135
00:09:28,415 --> 00:09:30,136
I've reached my limit.

136
00:09:30,340 --> 00:09:35,640
But I'm so close to being promoted
to Head of the Clinical Department.

137
00:09:35,920 --> 00:09:38,026
Then I'd have more time for the family.

138
00:09:38,066 --> 00:09:41,600
Enough. You don't understand anything.

139
00:09:51,703 --> 00:09:54,103
A last chance for Dr. Daikoku?

140
00:09:54,170 --> 00:09:58,883
Since we couldn't fire Dr. Anno,
she needs a watchdog.

141
00:09:58,970 --> 00:10:00,962
Indeed! Brilliant, Director!

142
00:10:01,002 --> 00:10:05,796
Wonderful insight and wonderful... something!
I'm truly in awe!

143
00:10:06,170 --> 00:10:09,150
If the ER closes, he loses his job, too.

144
00:10:09,190 --> 00:10:10,490
Indeed. Brilliant.

145
00:10:10,950 --> 00:10:14,570
Oh, Chairwoman! Where are you headed?

146
00:10:15,556 --> 00:10:18,443
I'm meeting with Mr. Nakazono
of the Liberal Democratic Party.

147
00:10:18,676 --> 00:10:22,170
Oh, Secretary Nakazono!
Allow me to accompany you.

148
00:10:22,210 --> 00:10:26,390
No need. Dr. Tamon arranged today's meeting.

149
00:10:26,430 --> 00:10:27,430
What?

150
00:10:27,456 --> 00:10:30,570
Director Fudo, please take charge
in my absence.

151
00:10:41,930 --> 00:10:46,856
Have you told Anno
about the plan to close the ER?

152
00:10:47,116 --> 00:10:48,116
Yes.

153
00:10:48,150 --> 00:10:49,576
What did she say?

154
00:10:49,710 --> 00:10:51,710
Anno's opinion is irrelevant.

155
00:10:53,190 --> 00:10:56,358
Maybe so. But Dr. Tamon...

156
00:10:56,462 --> 00:11:00,308
Do you really want to close the ER?

157
00:11:02,650 --> 00:11:05,663
I believe that's the best course of action.

158
00:11:07,910 --> 00:11:10,850
Tamon's been awfully cozy
with the chairwoman lately.

159
00:11:10,950 --> 00:11:14,270
At this rate, he might steal
the director position at the new hospital.

160
00:11:15,370 --> 00:11:17,190
We must do something immediately.

161
00:11:17,356 --> 00:11:21,143
Director, I have an idea.

162
00:11:22,076 --> 00:11:25,490
Leave everything to me, Matayoshi Kongo!

163
00:11:25,789 --> 00:11:29,770
I'd expect nothing less, Dr. Kongo.
I look forward to it.

164
00:11:29,810 --> 00:11:31,876
L... Look forward to it...

165
00:11:49,663 --> 00:11:52,905
All done. Take care on your way home, okay?

166
00:11:52,945 --> 00:11:54,570
Thank you, Doctor.

167
00:11:56,800 --> 00:11:58,153
Take care.

168
00:12:00,699 --> 00:12:02,233
- Kuyo.
- Yes?

169
00:12:02,322 --> 00:12:06,240
Tonight, if Anno tries to take
a critical patient, stop her.

170
00:12:06,280 --> 00:12:10,770
What? I can't do that!
Tell Dr. Anno yourself.

171
00:12:10,880 --> 00:12:13,363
Then call me if it happens.

172
00:12:13,403 --> 00:12:14,420
What?

173
00:12:14,460 --> 00:12:17,656
I'm counting on you. Please, I mean it.

174
00:12:22,183 --> 00:12:23,710
Can you fill these out?

175
00:12:24,040 --> 00:12:27,303
Wait, hold on. Let's talk about this.

176
00:12:27,510 --> 00:12:32,316
Shota understands, too.
I can't do this with you anymore.

177
00:12:36,616 --> 00:12:39,940
What? Dr. Daikoku asked something like that
before going home.

178
00:12:39,980 --> 00:12:42,720
It won't work though, when Dr. Ashura's here.

179
00:12:48,650 --> 00:12:49,943
Incoming.

180
00:13:01,720 --> 00:13:02,956
Kid, hurry!

181
00:13:03,340 --> 00:13:04,680
We'll examine your chest.

182
00:13:04,720 --> 00:13:06,183
We're here.

183
00:13:06,380 --> 00:13:07,860
Can you understand me?

184
00:13:07,900 --> 00:13:10,116
Can you hear me? Can you tell me your name?

185
00:13:12,293 --> 00:13:13,293
Vitals?

186
00:13:13,319 --> 00:13:17,605
BP 100, heart rate 130, saturation 98.
Consciousness level is in the double digits.

187
00:13:17,645 --> 00:13:19,826
Prep the CBC and chemistry panel.
Start two lines.

188
00:13:20,276 --> 00:13:22,180
Massive left retroperitoneal hematoma.

189
00:13:22,220 --> 00:13:24,200
Bleeding from the back side?

190
00:13:24,240 --> 00:13:26,536
We need to stop it
to avoid hemorrhagic shock.

191
00:13:26,882 --> 00:13:27,882
The X-ray is here.

192
00:13:27,909 --> 00:13:29,110
Chest and pelvis, hurry.

193
00:13:30,553 --> 00:13:31,840
Hemothorax in the left lung.

194
00:13:31,880 --> 00:13:33,422
There's bleeding from the lung, too?

195
00:13:33,462 --> 00:13:35,380
This way, he'll go into respiratory failure.

196
00:13:35,420 --> 00:13:37,700
Doctor! The head bleeding won't stop!

197
00:13:37,740 --> 00:13:39,540
Keep pressure on it. Prep for surgery now.

198
00:13:39,580 --> 00:13:42,580
We can't do this alone.
Call Surgery for backup!

199
00:13:42,620 --> 00:13:46,163
Doctor! An ICU patient self-extubated
and can't breathe!

200
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:48,120
She can't go there right now.

201
00:13:48,180 --> 00:13:50,480
What are you saying? The patient will die!

202
00:13:50,520 --> 00:13:52,320
This patient's dying, too!

203
00:13:52,360 --> 00:13:53,916
Then what do we do?

204
00:13:57,356 --> 00:13:59,450
Dr. Anno, your orders please.

205
00:14:01,756 --> 00:14:02,756
Vitals?

206
00:14:02,783 --> 00:14:06,596
BP 125, pulse 109, saturation 99.

207
00:14:13,796 --> 00:14:14,850
Three minutes.

208
00:14:14,890 --> 00:14:15,890
Huh?

209
00:14:15,916 --> 00:14:17,883
I'll treat him when I'm back.
Call a surgeon.

210
00:14:18,486 --> 00:14:20,179
Wait!

211
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:23,480
Doctor! Let's call for backup!

212
00:14:23,840 --> 00:14:25,076
Oh, right.

213
00:14:29,573 --> 00:14:30,573
Yes?

214
00:14:30,600 --> 00:14:32,443
Excuse me! ER here!

215
00:14:32,580 --> 00:14:33,580
What's going on?

216
00:14:33,606 --> 00:14:37,350
We need help. We have a patient in their 70s
with multiple traumatic injuries.

217
00:14:37,390 --> 00:14:39,790
Oh, that sounds serious.
I'll come help right away.

218
00:14:39,880 --> 00:14:42,106
Really? Thank you so much!

219
00:14:42,146 --> 00:14:47,736
But I'm swamped right now
and can't step away just yet.

220
00:14:49,780 --> 00:14:52,690
Have a CT done before I get there.

221
00:14:52,730 --> 00:14:55,530
Wait, I thought you were coming right now...

222
00:15:01,210 --> 00:15:03,350
Macaron, canelé, macaron...

223
00:15:03,390 --> 00:15:08,122
Macaron, then a lollipop...
Kidding, shortcake.

224
00:15:12,520 --> 00:15:15,140
Oh yeah, nice, nice.

225
00:15:15,570 --> 00:15:18,000
Delicious.

226
00:15:19,810 --> 00:15:21,996
Doctor, what should we do?

227
00:15:23,016 --> 00:15:24,220
CT.

228
00:15:24,423 --> 00:15:26,523
I need to check with Dr. Anno.

229
00:15:28,620 --> 00:15:29,822
Oxygen saturation at 70!

230
00:15:29,862 --> 00:15:31,068
Reintubating. Laryngoscope.

231
00:15:31,108 --> 00:15:32,310
Yes!

232
00:15:36,040 --> 00:15:37,290
She's not answering!

233
00:15:37,640 --> 00:15:40,000
Hesitation on the battlefield is fatal.

234
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:46,300
Resident or not, take responsibility
for the patient in front of you.

235
00:15:51,676 --> 00:15:55,930
Tachycardia, but oxygen saturation is stable.

236
00:16:00,200 --> 00:16:02,060
Let's take him to CT now.

237
00:16:02,100 --> 00:16:04,080
Shouldn't we check with Dr. Anno?

238
00:16:04,120 --> 00:16:06,930
She'll need the data, too. Hurry.

239
00:16:10,900 --> 00:16:12,433
What happened?

240
00:16:12,473 --> 00:16:14,813
Laryngeal edema. Can't reintubate.

241
00:16:14,883 --> 00:16:16,230
Prep for cricothyrotomy.

242
00:16:16,270 --> 00:16:17,483
Understood!

243
00:16:28,900 --> 00:16:30,250
Stop, please!

244
00:16:34,803 --> 00:16:36,090
- Take it.
- Okay.

245
00:16:38,503 --> 00:16:39,503
What?

246
00:16:39,529 --> 00:16:41,803
Doctor, the patient's gone into shock!

247
00:16:41,870 --> 00:16:44,450
CT room! Come here now, please!

248
00:16:44,490 --> 00:16:46,763
I can't. Surgical airway in progress.

249
00:16:47,336 --> 00:16:49,016
Why are you even doing a CT?

250
00:16:49,056 --> 00:16:52,036
Dr. Kongo told me to get one!

251
00:16:52,830 --> 00:16:55,102
I checked with the paramedics.

252
00:16:55,142 --> 00:16:58,883
The patient is an old man with no family.
No risk of a lawsuit if he dies.

253
00:16:59,410 --> 00:17:04,136
Ordering scans without seeing the patient.
He never planned to treat him.

254
00:17:05,030 --> 00:17:07,795
If the ER lets a patient die,

255
00:17:07,835 --> 00:17:11,445
we can pin all the blame on Dr. Tamon.

256
00:17:11,683 --> 00:17:13,670
That way, we can force him out.

257
00:17:13,930 --> 00:17:19,130
Director, leave everything
to me, Matayoshi Kongo!

258
00:17:20,010 --> 00:17:23,356
Don't underestimate me.
Keep him alive until I get there!

259
00:17:23,396 --> 00:17:24,603
What?!

260
00:17:26,422 --> 00:17:27,422
But how?

261
00:17:27,449 --> 00:17:30,843
Blood's pooling in the chest,
causing respiratory failure. Intubate now.

262
00:17:30,883 --> 00:17:35,390
I can't intubate! Please, help me!

263
00:17:35,430 --> 00:17:38,923
You're the only one who can save him. Man up!

264
00:17:42,323 --> 00:17:45,363
Dr. Anno? Dr. Anno!

265
00:17:48,743 --> 00:17:51,076
Oxygen saturation is dropping fast!

266
00:17:51,610 --> 00:17:54,930
Come on, go back up.

267
00:18:07,322 --> 00:18:08,576
I'm going to intubate!

268
00:18:10,036 --> 00:18:12,020
Tamotsu, have you done this before?

269
00:18:12,060 --> 00:18:17,113
Only on a mannequin in med school.
But I have no choice.

270
00:18:19,500 --> 00:18:20,910
Laryngoscope, please.

271
00:18:42,850 --> 00:18:44,385
It won't go in.

272
00:18:47,123 --> 00:18:49,420
Why won't it go in?

273
00:18:50,620 --> 00:18:53,129
Hurry, or he'll die!

274
00:18:56,180 --> 00:18:58,047
Doctor! Saturation is at 70!

275
00:18:58,087 --> 00:18:59,453
I know that!

276
00:18:59,493 --> 00:19:04,292
Get in! Get in! Get in! Please, get in!

277
00:19:04,332 --> 00:19:06,190
It's at 60!

278
00:19:06,230 --> 00:19:07,436
Get in!

279
00:19:08,303 --> 00:19:09,603
Please, get in...

280
00:19:19,083 --> 00:19:20,283
What's wrong?

281
00:19:21,736 --> 00:19:22,938
I can't.

282
00:19:29,809 --> 00:19:32,250
I knew it. I just can't do this.

283
00:19:32,930 --> 00:19:34,145
What do you mean?

284
00:19:34,916 --> 00:19:36,956
You're the only doctor here!

285
00:19:36,996 --> 00:19:39,303
I'm telling you, I can't!

286
00:19:43,490 --> 00:19:44,905
Dr. Anno.

287
00:19:47,090 --> 00:19:48,945
Please help me.

288
00:19:53,150 --> 00:19:54,730
- Take over here!
- Yes!

289
00:19:55,790 --> 00:19:56,990
Damn it!

290
00:20:25,630 --> 00:20:28,911
Well then, shall I head over soon?

291
00:20:30,760 --> 00:20:34,350
To bask in Ashura's anguished expression.

292
00:20:35,286 --> 00:20:36,500
Time for a haiku!

293
00:20:37,720 --> 00:20:42,740
On the battlefield,
twisted in pure agony... It is Ashura.

294
00:20:43,640 --> 00:20:48,560
How are you?
Ashura on the battlefield, shura-shu-shu-shu!

295
00:20:50,800 --> 00:20:54,118
Oops, maybe I shouldn't be laughing.

296
00:20:55,990 --> 00:20:57,190
Go!

297
00:20:58,420 --> 00:21:01,796
Sorry, I'm late! How's the patient... Huh?

298
00:21:05,930 --> 00:21:09,170
Tamon?! No way!

299
00:21:10,230 --> 00:21:12,990
Don't tell me they're operating in here?

300
00:21:13,210 --> 00:21:15,096
Blood clot on the dorsal side of the hilum.

301
00:21:15,136 --> 00:21:16,510
Finding the bleed source.

302
00:21:17,783 --> 00:21:19,530
Doctor! The bleeding...!

303
00:21:19,570 --> 00:21:22,183
- Clamping it. Long forceps and long Kocher.
- Here!

304
00:21:35,400 --> 00:21:36,703
It stopped.

305
00:21:37,530 --> 00:21:38,900
Endo GIA stapler.

306
00:21:39,076 --> 00:21:40,140
Yes!

307
00:21:40,180 --> 00:21:42,785
Release it, then redo the Satinsky clamp.

308
00:21:42,825 --> 00:21:44,030
Right.

309
00:21:50,910 --> 00:21:52,510
- Hold.
- Now.

310
00:21:57,403 --> 00:22:02,920
These two are incredible. Perfectly in sync.

311
00:22:12,100 --> 00:22:13,303
Done.

312
00:22:27,690 --> 00:22:32,710
Tell the director I said thanks.
I enjoyed this battlefield...

313
00:22:34,510 --> 00:22:36,350
Oh, no...

314
00:22:42,403 --> 00:22:44,100
Ta... Tamon!

315
00:22:45,543 --> 00:22:49,323
For now, his respiratory
and circulatory status is stable.

316
00:22:49,436 --> 00:22:50,540
Good to hear.

317
00:22:50,580 --> 00:22:52,236
The rest is yours, Dr. Kongo.

318
00:22:52,576 --> 00:22:55,963
Of course! Leave it to Matayoshi Kongo...

319
00:23:32,610 --> 00:23:33,909
Why did you help?

320
00:23:36,950 --> 00:23:39,150
You said you'd shut down the ER.

321
00:23:41,576 --> 00:23:46,983
I never said I wanted
to abandon patients brought to the ER.

322
00:23:47,570 --> 00:23:48,776
Then...

323
00:23:50,350 --> 00:23:52,070
Why shut it down?

324
00:24:00,543 --> 00:24:01,796
The promise...

325
00:24:05,530 --> 00:24:09,376
Have you forgotten our promise?

326
00:24:13,440 --> 00:24:17,843
When I come back, let's change
emergency medicine in Japan together.

327
00:25:28,803 --> 00:25:32,216
I intend to shut down the ER.

328
00:25:41,730 --> 00:25:43,890
Hey, wait...!

329
00:25:45,750 --> 00:25:46,956
What?

330
00:25:47,216 --> 00:25:50,116
Did something happen
between you and Dr. Tamon?

331
00:25:51,143 --> 00:25:52,390
Nothing.

332
00:25:54,050 --> 00:25:59,203
I just wondered if maybe
he said something to you again.

333
00:26:00,850 --> 00:26:02,056
Again?

334
00:26:03,609 --> 00:26:06,783
- What do you mean?
- Well, the other day...

335
00:26:07,836 --> 00:26:11,610
I overheard Dr. Tamon saying
the ER is getting shut down.

336
00:26:15,683 --> 00:26:16,963
Are you okay?

337
00:26:19,363 --> 00:26:21,300
That's not for you to worry about, Kid.

338
00:26:21,536 --> 00:26:22,749
But...

339
00:26:23,943 --> 00:26:27,896
Dr. Tamon betrayed the ER, didn't he?

340
00:26:29,620 --> 00:26:34,353
Even though you were fighting all alone
the entire time he was gone!

341
00:26:34,393 --> 00:26:38,810
A kid who can't even treat patients alone has
no business worrying about me!

342
00:26:49,530 --> 00:26:51,816
Master how to do intubation by tomorrow.

343
00:27:03,843 --> 00:27:05,810
- Dr. Daikoku.
- The patient?

344
00:27:05,850 --> 00:27:08,590
Dr. Kongo came and admitted
the patient to surgery.

345
00:27:10,623 --> 00:27:14,590
I'm terribly sorry
I couldn't meet your expectations!

346
00:27:14,630 --> 00:27:17,303
I never expected Tamon to come to the rescue.

347
00:27:17,650 --> 00:27:18,790
Damn it!

348
00:27:18,830 --> 00:27:20,096
Damn it!

349
00:27:20,190 --> 00:27:23,310
And Ashura's still doing
whatever she pleases!

350
00:27:23,350 --> 00:27:26,676
We should've had her fired by now.

351
00:27:32,406 --> 00:27:33,606
This is terrible...

352
00:27:34,610 --> 00:27:36,830
I'm so sorry!

353
00:27:36,870 --> 00:27:40,615
What the hell is going on?
Get that woman under control!

354
00:27:40,655 --> 00:27:41,890
I apologize for the trouble.

355
00:27:41,930 --> 00:27:45,830
Dr. Daikoku, I'm disappointed in you.

356
00:27:45,870 --> 00:27:53,603
I'll give Anno a stern warning!
Just please, don't demote me!

357
00:27:55,130 --> 00:27:59,530
As I've said many times, our policy is
not to accept critical patients.

358
00:28:01,310 --> 00:28:03,310
Organizational rules are absolute.

359
00:28:04,736 --> 00:28:06,076
You understand that, right?

360
00:28:31,135 --> 00:28:34,715
Anno, do you have any idea what you've done?

361
00:28:34,755 --> 00:28:36,910
I didn't do anything wrong.

362
00:28:37,343 --> 00:28:42,543
Surgery filed a complaint
that you forced them to come to the ER.

363
00:28:42,583 --> 00:28:44,950
Forced? That's a lie!

364
00:28:44,990 --> 00:28:48,016
He barely showed up at all!
The patient almost died!

365
00:28:48,056 --> 00:28:52,270
I've told you not to accept
critical patients!

366
00:28:52,310 --> 00:28:55,770
But that patient had already been rejected
by four other hospitals.

367
00:28:56,070 --> 00:28:58,275
If we'd refused too, he'd definitely be dead!

368
00:28:58,315 --> 00:29:00,256
I don't care about that!

369
00:29:04,110 --> 00:29:07,816
Don't tell me you're all falling
under Anno's influence now.

370
00:29:08,190 --> 00:29:10,576
This is a hospital! An organization!

371
00:29:10,990 --> 00:29:12,870
Orders from above are absolute!

372
00:29:12,910 --> 00:29:14,463
That's enough!

373
00:29:17,580 --> 00:29:21,843
Why can't you just be happy
that the patient survived?

374
00:29:33,650 --> 00:29:34,990
Doctor, please wait.

375
00:29:38,110 --> 00:29:40,070
Kid, let's go to the ICU.

376
00:29:49,309 --> 00:29:50,509
Incoming.

377
00:30:04,633 --> 00:30:07,966
One pediatric patient from a car accident.
Requesting admission.

378
00:30:08,006 --> 00:30:10,769
BP unreadable,
consciousness level around GCS three.

379
00:30:10,890 --> 00:30:12,110
Bring them in.

380
00:30:12,820 --> 00:30:15,560
Stop. That patient's beyond
what we can handle.

381
00:30:16,020 --> 00:30:18,156
You wouldn't see any patient.

382
00:30:18,560 --> 00:30:19,960
It's a child!

383
00:30:20,020 --> 00:30:23,520
If we accept and then something happens,
we could face a lawsuit!

384
00:30:25,462 --> 00:30:26,669
Refuse them. Now.

385
00:30:33,600 --> 00:30:35,173
How many times must I say it?

386
00:30:35,800 --> 00:30:39,316
Our policy is to refuse critical patients!

387
00:30:40,287 --> 00:30:42,753
Hospital rules are absolute!

388
00:30:49,310 --> 00:30:50,690
Darling, help!

389
00:30:50,850 --> 00:30:52,383
It's Shota!

390
00:30:54,056 --> 00:30:55,910
Ma'am, please calm down!

391
00:31:00,828 --> 00:31:01,836
Kaori?

392
00:31:01,876 --> 00:31:06,120
No hospital will take him!
Shota's going to die!

393
00:31:06,596 --> 00:31:10,163
- Shota?
- Please, save him!

394
00:31:12,266 --> 00:31:14,006
Can you accept the patient?

395
00:31:16,546 --> 00:31:17,768
We don't have...

396
00:31:19,246 --> 00:31:22,183
We have no one
who can treat pediatric trauma.

397
00:31:24,863 --> 00:31:29,180
Can you take him
to Touou University Hospital's trauma center?

398
00:31:29,220 --> 00:31:31,483
They turned us away. No beds available.

399
00:31:33,419 --> 00:31:35,306
All nearby hospitals have refused!

400
00:31:35,310 --> 00:31:37,123
We don't have any other options!

401
00:31:37,932 --> 00:31:39,212
Shota!

402
00:31:50,290 --> 00:31:52,376
We'll take him. Bring him in now.

403
00:31:52,416 --> 00:31:53,530
Stop!

404
00:31:53,570 --> 00:31:54,790
We can't save him here...

405
00:31:54,830 --> 00:31:56,143
He's your son, isn't he?

406
00:32:00,220 --> 00:32:02,660
I will pull him back
from the battlefield.

407
00:32:14,136 --> 00:32:15,160
Get ready. Now.

408
00:32:15,200 --> 00:32:16,410
Yes!

409
00:32:30,850 --> 00:32:32,730
- On three.
- One, two, three!

410
00:32:32,770 --> 00:32:34,770
Two lines in, fluids at full rate.

411
00:32:34,810 --> 00:32:36,083
- Cutting his clothes.
- Vitals?

412
00:32:36,123 --> 00:32:40,130
Blood pressure 70, pulse 150.
Saturation is 88% with a four-liter mask.

413
00:32:40,170 --> 00:32:43,623
Pale face with tachycardia,
low blood pressure, and in shock.

414
00:32:43,750 --> 00:32:45,470
The cause of the shock is...

415
00:32:48,646 --> 00:32:49,920
Blunt trauma.

416
00:32:50,320 --> 00:32:52,173
His organs are damaged?!

417
00:33:02,860 --> 00:33:04,840
Doctor, BP's dropped to 60!

418
00:33:04,880 --> 00:33:07,080
- We operate now. Call for anesthesia.
- OK!

419
00:33:07,120 --> 00:33:08,326
Prep for transfusion.

420
00:33:22,870 --> 00:33:24,170
- Scalpel.
- Here.

421
00:33:27,886 --> 00:33:28,940
- Retractor.
- Here.

422
00:33:28,980 --> 00:33:30,840
- Suction.
- Got it!

423
00:33:34,870 --> 00:33:36,080
Deeper!

424
00:33:36,220 --> 00:33:37,443
Got it!

425
00:33:39,300 --> 00:33:40,800
The spleen is damaged.

426
00:33:41,263 --> 00:33:42,680
Suturing. 3-0 Vicryl.

427
00:33:42,720 --> 00:33:43,943
Yes.

428
00:33:53,330 --> 00:33:54,530
Something's wrong.

429
00:33:55,456 --> 00:33:56,670
The bleeding won't stop.

430
00:33:57,083 --> 00:33:58,303
Long forceps and gauze.

431
00:33:58,430 --> 00:34:01,170
There's another bleeding source
besides the spleen?

432
00:34:18,265 --> 00:34:19,923
- Suction here.
- Got it!

433
00:34:20,623 --> 00:34:21,876
No, here!

434
00:34:22,296 --> 00:34:23,516
Hurry!

435
00:34:26,820 --> 00:34:29,433
Sorry! I'll change it!

436
00:34:35,656 --> 00:34:36,902
Where?

437
00:34:37,209 --> 00:34:39,769
Doctor, BP is dropping fast!

438
00:34:40,290 --> 00:34:41,576
Where is it?

439
00:34:42,510 --> 00:34:44,923
Where?! I can't see through the blood!

440
00:34:45,783 --> 00:34:46,996
Where is it?

441
00:34:51,743 --> 00:34:53,263
Where?!

442
00:35:11,350 --> 00:35:13,256
Dr. Daikoku.

443
00:35:14,069 --> 00:35:16,863
Let me help as well.

444
00:35:19,663 --> 00:35:21,636
Can you operate on your own child?

445
00:35:30,833 --> 00:35:32,073
I'm a doctor.

446
00:35:32,983 --> 00:35:34,283
I want to save my son.

447
00:35:37,090 --> 00:35:39,128
Open the surgical field
and find the bleeding point.

448
00:35:39,168 --> 00:35:40,168
Right.

449
00:35:40,194 --> 00:35:41,516
- Gauze.
- Here.

450
00:35:46,670 --> 00:35:48,250
Liver looks fine.

451
00:35:48,683 --> 00:35:49,870
Behind the stomach?

452
00:35:49,910 --> 00:35:51,156
- Kelly.
- Here.

453
00:36:05,513 --> 00:36:06,803
What is it?

454
00:36:08,526 --> 00:36:10,071
Over the portal vein...

455
00:36:11,234 --> 00:36:13,980
The pancreas has been completely severed.

456
00:36:14,199 --> 00:36:15,399
What?!

457
00:36:15,680 --> 00:36:17,600
He's already lost a lot of blood.

458
00:36:18,000 --> 00:36:19,573
We can't waste any more time.

459
00:36:19,826 --> 00:36:21,166
To stop the bleeding,

460
00:36:22,112 --> 00:36:24,154
we need to remove the distal pancreas.

461
00:36:24,699 --> 00:36:27,749
We have no choice but to remove it all.

462
00:36:28,156 --> 00:36:29,589
Remove it?

463
00:36:31,353 --> 00:36:32,589
Is that okay?

464
00:36:33,540 --> 00:36:34,960
He's only twelve!

465
00:36:35,000 --> 00:36:36,236
We have no choice!

466
00:36:36,410 --> 00:36:39,920
He'll need insulin for life,
but it's better than dying!

467
00:36:39,960 --> 00:36:41,166
What are you saying?

468
00:36:41,980 --> 00:36:43,196
We're not removing it.

469
00:36:43,819 --> 00:36:44,940
Huh?

470
00:36:44,980 --> 00:36:49,578
But in this situation, there's no way
to save him without resection!

471
00:36:51,900 --> 00:36:53,836
I'll do the Letton-Wilson procedure.

472
00:36:57,836 --> 00:37:00,002
Close the proximal pancreatic stump,

473
00:37:00,042 --> 00:37:04,042
debride the crushed tissue, and anastomose
the transected body to the jejunum.

474
00:37:04,082 --> 00:37:06,594
- We can preserve full pancreatic function.
- Impossible!

475
00:37:06,634 --> 00:37:09,085
No one here can perform
a surgery that complex.

476
00:37:09,125 --> 00:37:10,125
I can.

477
00:37:10,154 --> 00:37:11,154
But still...!

478
00:37:11,181 --> 00:37:15,949
Hesitation on the battlefield is fatal!
There's no time to waver! Help me!

479
00:37:23,380 --> 00:37:24,593
All right.

480
00:37:28,800 --> 00:37:30,240
Satinsky clamp and long forceps.

481
00:37:30,280 --> 00:37:31,500
Got it!

482
00:37:38,520 --> 00:37:39,940
I will save him!

483
00:38:40,266 --> 00:38:41,469
Thank you.

484
00:38:42,986 --> 00:38:45,113
For saving Shota.

485
00:38:48,773 --> 00:38:50,026
No.

486
00:38:51,240 --> 00:38:55,923
The truth is, I hesitated
to accept Shota as a patient.

487
00:38:57,309 --> 00:39:00,780
I wasn't confident I could save him.

488
00:39:04,016 --> 00:39:09,500
I'm a failure as both a doctor and a father.

489
00:39:13,990 --> 00:39:16,490
But you did save Shota's life.

490
00:39:20,569 --> 00:39:21,796
I realized something.

491
00:39:23,430 --> 00:39:29,503
This is how you've been saving
so many lives all along.

492
00:39:32,996 --> 00:39:34,816
The other day, Shota told me something.

493
00:39:36,130 --> 00:39:39,410
He said he wants to be
an emergency physician like his dad.

494
00:39:45,270 --> 00:39:50,450
Shota's been watching you all this time.

495
00:40:02,149 --> 00:40:05,603
From now on, for Shota's sake...

496
00:40:07,089 --> 00:40:08,576
I need to become

497
00:40:10,710 --> 00:40:13,283
a doctor he can be proud of.

498
00:40:17,716 --> 00:40:18,916
Yeah.

499
00:40:27,860 --> 00:40:31,420
I'm glad Shota's surgery went well.

500
00:40:31,843 --> 00:40:34,660
I can't believe she did
a Letton-Wilson procedure in the ER.

501
00:40:34,700 --> 00:40:36,916
Only Dr. Anno could pull that off.

502
00:40:36,956 --> 00:40:39,930
I realized emergency medicine is
truly amazing.

503
00:40:40,779 --> 00:40:45,183
You can actually save the life
of someone from your own family.

504
00:40:49,400 --> 00:40:52,556
So you're thinking of becoming
an emergency physician, too?

505
00:40:52,660 --> 00:40:54,856
No, that's absolutely impossible.

506
00:40:54,896 --> 00:40:59,763
I couldn't do anything again.
Someone like me can't do emergency medicine.

507
00:41:00,720 --> 00:41:03,709
Dr. Anno, why did you choose
emergency medicine?

508
00:41:06,850 --> 00:41:11,196
I just want to save patients.

509
00:41:14,460 --> 00:41:17,743
Dr. Anno really is amazing.

510
00:41:18,850 --> 00:41:20,309
So cool.

511
00:41:41,256 --> 00:41:42,470
Dad.

512
00:41:44,350 --> 00:41:45,630
Mom.

513
00:41:59,280 --> 00:42:00,480
Dad.

514
00:42:06,863 --> 00:42:08,283
Mom.

515
00:42:26,543 --> 00:42:27,929
Come in.

516
00:42:35,270 --> 00:42:36,483
What is it?

517
00:42:36,840 --> 00:42:40,446
I have a proposal regarding
the International Taishaku Hospital.

518
00:42:41,270 --> 00:42:43,490
Did you come up with a good idea?

519
00:42:43,530 --> 00:42:44,730
Yes.

520
00:42:44,903 --> 00:42:46,680
Please, tell me then.

521
00:42:48,129 --> 00:42:51,770
I never imagined we could enlist your help.

522
00:42:52,789 --> 00:42:54,483
It's most reassuring.

523
00:42:57,380 --> 00:43:01,943
I've heard of your achievements
since my days at Touou University Hospital.

524
00:43:03,453 --> 00:43:08,183
With your cooperation,
everything will go exactly as we plan.

525
00:43:08,340 --> 00:43:12,296
Of course. After all, my success rate is...

526
00:43:14,206 --> 00:43:16,593
at 99 percent.

527
00:43:53,696 --> 00:43:54,910
